<table class=reg width=100%><tr><td width=85%><b>&ldquo;</b>But even &ldquo;good&rdquo; metaphors don&rsquo;t always work. For instance, in an informal survey of <a href="guis/macos">Macintosh</a>-literate university students, many people failed to employ the word &ldquo;desktop&rdquo; anywhere in their description of the Finder.<b>&rdquo;</b></td><td width=15% align=right valign=top><a href='guis/macos'><img align=right width=32 height=32 border=0 title='Mac OS' alt='Mac OS' src='intr/osicons/macos.png'></a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 align=right> (Brenda Laurel, &ldquo;Computers as theatre,&rdquo; p. 5, 1993)</td></tr></table><br clear=all><br><br><table class=reg width=100%><tr><td width=85%><b>&ldquo;</b>My favorite <a href="guis/macos">Macintosh</a> example is an error message that I sometimes encounter while running Multifinder: &ldquo;Excel (or some other application) has unexpectedly quit.&rdquo; &ldquo;Well,&rdquo; I usually reply, &ldquo;the capricious little bastard!&rdquo;<b>&rdquo;</b></td><td width=15% align=right valign=top><a href='guis/macos'><img align=right width=32 height=32 border=0 title='Mac OS' alt='Mac OS' src='intr/osicons/macos.png'></a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 align=right> (Brenda Laurel, &ldquo;Computers as theatre,&rdquo; p. 63, 1993)</td></tr></table><br clear=all><br><br><table class=reg width=100%><tr><td width=85%><b>&ldquo;</b>No. It&rsquo;s no evolution at all. It&rsquo;s no advance at all. [The users are still] stuck in this morass of overlapping windows.<b>&rdquo;</b></td><td width=15% align=right valign=top><a href='guis/macos'><img align=right width=32 height=32 border=0 title='Mac OS' alt='Mac OS' src='intr/osicons/macos.png'></a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 align=right> (Jef Raskin on <a href="guis/macos/macosx">Mac OS X</a>)</td></tr></table><br clear=all><br><br><table class=reg width=100%><tr><td width=85%><b>&ldquo;</b>The <a href="guis/nextstep">NeXT</a> machine&rsquo;s &ldquo;black hole&rdquo; icon is an interesting alternative [to <a href="guis/macos">Macintosh</a>&rsquo;s trash can], but <i>as a metaphor</i> it suggests a disturbing irreversibility. One can, after all, take things back out of a trash can &ndash; usually.<b>&rdquo;</b></td><td width=15% align=right valign=top><a href='guis/macos'><img align=right width=32 height=32 border=0 title='Mac OS' alt='Mac OS' src='intr/osicons/macos.png'></a><a href='guis/nextstep'><img align=right width=32 height=32 border=0 title='NeXTSTEP/OPENSTEP/Rhapsody' alt='NeXTSTEP/OPENSTEP/Rhapsody' src='intr/osicons/nextstep.png'></a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 align=right> (Brenda Laurel, &ldquo;Computers as theatre,&rdquo; p. 131, 1993)</td></tr></table><br clear=all><br><br><table class=reg width=100%><tr><td width=85%><b>&ldquo;</b>Whatever Apple&rsquo;s plans are, we think it extremely unlikely that it would introduce a similar product that would undercut their <a href="guis/lisa">Lisa</a> system so soon after its costly development and introduction. Indeed, we cannot see the benefit that would be gained by such action. So, whatever MacIntosh [sic] may turn out to be and whenever it finally appears, we think it is more likely that it will be clearly differentiated from the Lisa offering.<b>&rdquo;</b></td><td width=15% align=right valign=top><a href='guis/lisa'><img align=right width=32 height=32 border=0 title='Lisa Office System' alt='Lisa Office System' src='intr/osicons/lisa.png'></a><a href='guis/macos'><img align=right width=32 height=32 border=0 title='Mac OS' alt='Mac OS' src='intr/osicons/macos.png'></a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 align=right> (Joseph L. Ehardt, The Seybold Report on Professional Computing, January 1983)</td></tr></table><br clear=all><br><br></td><td height=50 style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)'><img width=12 height=1 src='intr/3rightfill.png'></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td height=30><img width=50 height=30 hspace=0 src='intr/31bottomleft.png'></td><td height=30 width=100% style='background: url(intr/31bottomfill.png)'></td><td height=30><img width=47 height=30 hspace=0 src='intr/31bottomclosed.png'></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><table width=100% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td valign=top width=50 style='background: url(intr/1leftfill.png) top left repeat-y'><img width=50 src='intr/1leftfill.png'></td><td width=100% class=box1text>
